                            <comment id="17681693" author="godfrey" created="Sun, 29 Jan 2023 07:54:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=zhuzh&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;zhuzh&quot;&gt;zhuzh&lt;/a&gt; thanks for reporting this issue.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Currently, the parallelism of global sort is set as 1, but the max parallelism is not set because ExecNodeBase#inputsContainSingleton does not work for global sort.&#160; This works fine for the default scheduler, but may occur wrong result if &#160;adaptive batch scheduler changes the global sort parallelism.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I will fix it.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
